Detailed Description

Listener class for handling when a map object has been selected in the map, for instance by clicking.

virtual void WFAPI::SelectedMapObjectListener::handleSelectedMapObject ( const MapObjectInfo &  mapObjectInfo,
OverlayItem *  overlayItem,
const WGS84Coordinate &  coord,
bool  longPress 
) [pure virtual]

Handle that a map object has been selected in the map. In case an OverlayItem has been selected, then a pointer to the OverlayItem is supplied as a parameter, otherwise NULL.

Parameters:
mapObjectInfo MapObjectInfo containing details about the selected map object (always set).
overlayItem In case an OverlayItem was selected, then a pointer to the OverlayItem will be passed as parameter, otherwise NULL.
coord The coordinate for the selected object.
longPress True if the selection was the result of a long press action.
